President Biden spoke with President Lopez Obrador of Mexico to discuss strengthening the U.S.-Mexico bilateral relationship. They focused on managing migration in the region, with an emphasis on cooperation between the two countries' border authorities and enforcement measures. Both leaders highlighted the importance of managing migration in a humane and orderly way, while also addressing the root causes of migration from Central America. They also discussed reducing crowding in northern Mexico and continuing their joint initiative to decrease border encounters. Additionally, they acknowledged efforts to counter illicit fentanyl and arms trafficking, as well as their commitment to modernizing the shared border and promoting economic growth.